Package ides.api.plugin.presentation

Interface UIDescriptor

  • public interface UIDescriptor
    The descriptor of what UI elements will be available to the user when a model is activated. This descriptor is constructed by the Toolset for the specific type of model.
    See Also:
    Toolset

    • Method Detail

      • getMainPanePresentations

        Presentation[] getMainPanePresentations()
        Retrieve the list of Presentations to be added to the main pane of the IDES interface when the model is activated. Each Presentation will be added in a separate tab.

        Note: This method may be called multiple times for the same model, so new Presentations should not be instantiated at each call.

        Returns:
        the list of Presentations to be added to the main pane of the IDES interface

      • getLeftPanePresentations

        Presentation[] getLeftPanePresentations()
        As of IDES version 3, this method does nothing.

        Retrieve the list of Presentations to appear on the left side of the main pane of IDES when the model is activated. Each Presentation will be added in a separate tab.

        Note: This method may be called multiple times for the same model, so new Presentations should not be instantiated at each call.

        Returns:
        the list of Presentations to appear on the left side of the main pane of IDES

      • getRightPanePresentations

        Presentation[] getRightPanePresentations()
        Retrieve the list of Presentations to appear on the right side of the main pane of IDES when the model is activated. Each Presentation will be added in a separate tab.

        Note: This method may be called multiple times for the same model, so new Presentations should not be instantiated at each call.

        Returns:
        the list of Presentations to appear on the right side of the main pane of IDES

      • getMenus

        javax.swing.JMenu[] getMenus()
        Retrieve the menus to be added to the IDES menu when the model is activated.

        Note: This method may be called multiple times for the same model, so new menus should not be instantiated at each call.

        Returns:

      • getToolbar

        javax.swing.JToolBar getToolbar()
        Retrieve a toolbar with icons to be added to the IDES toolbar when the model is activated.

        Note: This method may be called multiple times for the same model, so a new toolbar should not be instantiated at each call.

        Returns:
        the toolbar with icons to be added to the IDES toolbar

        Returns:
        the Presentation which will be added to the status bar of IDES
        See Also:
        Hub.getUserInterface(), UserInterface.getStatusBar()
